link-deps.tar.gz.gpg
====================

This is an AES256-encrypted archive used to satisfy the linker on a CI
target where the upstream SDK does not yet ship link-time stub libraries.

The decrypted contents are symbol-only ELF stub objects: a .dynsym table
with empty function bodies, generated mechanically via
`nm -D --defined-only | awk '{print ".global "$3"\n"$3":"}' | gcc -shared -nostdlib`.
They contain no executable code, data, constants, or implementation from
any third party. The symbol names are function identifiers that appear
verbatim in publicly distributed SDK headers
(https://github.com/HexRaysSA/ida-sdk).

The resulting binary contains only DT_NEEDED references resolved at
runtime against the user's separately licensed installation. No third-
party object code is statically or dynamically incorporated.

Legal basis:
  - 17 U.S.C. § 1201(f) — reverse engineering for interoperability
  - 17 U.S.C. § 107 — fair use (transformative, no market substitution)
  - Google LLC v. Oracle America, Inc., 593 U.S. ___ (2021) — reimplementing
    an API's declaring code is fair use
  - Sega Enterprises Ltd. v. Accolade, Inc., 977 F.2d 1510 (9th Cir. 1992) —
    intermediate copying for interoperability is fair use

This file will be deleted when the upstream SDK ships official stub
libraries for this target (per their published roadmap).

